Problem:
Find the area of triangle $ABC$ below.


[asy]

unitsize(1inch);

pair P,Q,R;

P = (0,0);

Q= (sqrt(3),0);

R = (0,1);

draw (P--Q--R--P,linewidth(0.9));

draw(rightanglemark(Q,P,R,3));

label("$A$",P,S);

label("$B$",Q,S);

label("$C$",R,N);

label("$6$",R/2,W);

label("$30^\circ$",(1.25,0),N);

[/asy]

generated_answer:
Solution:
Triangle $ABC$ is a 30-60-90 triangle with hypotenuse $BC = 6.$  Therefore, $AB = 3$ and $AC = 3 \sqrt{3}.$

[asy]

unitsize(1inch);

pair P,Q,R;

P = (0,0);

Q= (sqrt(3),0);

R = (0,1);

draw (P--Q--R--P,linewidth(0.9));

draw(rightanglemark(Q,P,R,3));

label("$A$",P,S);

label("$B$",Q,S);

label("$C$",R,N);

label("$6$",R/2,W);

label("$3$",(P + Q)/2,S);

label("$3\sqrt{3}$",(P + R)/2,W);

label("$30^\circ$",(1.25,0),N);

[/asy]

Therefore, the area of triangle $ABC$ is $\frac{1}{2} \cdot 3 \cdot 3 \sqrt{3} = \boxed{\frac{9 \sqrt{3}}{2}}.$

